#photocompetition - Are you ready to immortalise and tell your story of the #viaFrancigena?

The #entries to the photo competition “Through the Eyes of a Pilgrim” are open. 
The scope of the #contest, which is #free and open to everyone, is to interpret the Via Francigena with the eyes of 'a pilgrim', i.e.: the wonder and emotions felt by whoever decides to undertake this journey. The #theme of the competition can be freely interpreted , but the #photographs have to be both unpublished and relevant to the subject; you can photograph with analogical or digital cameras or smart-phones, the photographs have to liberally interpret the subject “Pilgrims of the Third Millenium”. #Participating is very easy: just send your #photos (maximum 3) to contest@lunicafoto.it – with the name and surname of the #photographer, and title of the photographs, locations and date that these were taken, along with a telephone number of the participant. The closing date for the competition will be on the 20th July 2017, anything posted after this date will not be considered. From the aforementioned date a panel of experts will select the three best photographs. For the winners there are some fantastic prizes. First #prize is 3 nights at the beautiful #Castle of the #Piagnaro in #Pontremoli and a print of the winning photograph; second prize is a supper for two at a local restaurant and third prize a hamper of food and specialities from #Lunigiana. The awards ceremony will take place on Sunday, 30th July, 2017 at 6.00pm at the Convento dei Padri Cappuccini in Pontremoli #contest #photography #pilgrims #pilgrim #pellegrini #en #enjoy #share #aevf #shot
